{"title":"maxon motors make their way from Mars to e-bikes w/ ‘Invisible’ Bikedrive Air e-bike Motor","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/07/01/maxon-bikedrive-air/","date":1625158829000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p><span>There’s no doubt that e-bikes are gaining popularity </span><span>worldwide</span><span>. With that increase, we’re seeing more companies jumping into the ring for e-bike propulsion as well as the bicycles themselves. Now, with a lengthy history of powering the Mars Exploration Program and shortly after their motors flew the first Martian helicopter, maxon is launching a new motor – for e-bikes. With its new Bikedrive Air, maxon seeks to streamline some clunky aspects of the e-bike user experience.&nbsp;</span></p><p><span><iframe width=\"696\" height=\"392\" data-ezsrc=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/JDjGRaqgi9I?version=3&amp;rel=1&amp;showsearch=0&amp;showinfo=1&amp;iv_load_policy=1&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en-US&amp;autohide=2&amp;start=15&amp;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\" ezoid=\"0.16800780928896164\"></iframe></span></p><p><span>maxon leverages 60 years of electric motor design for the 7.7-pound system. It fits “invisibly” inside a wide array of frame designs — racing, gravel, urban, and kids’ frames are all in play. The mid-mounted motor gives riders a natural riding feel by balancing weight. According to maxon, the rider experience is “like riding with a tailwind.”&nbsp;</span></p><p><span>Stats are middle-of-the-road, but the rider experience promises to be unique. Here’s our first look at the maxon Bikedrive Air.&nbsp;</span></p><h2>Invisibility Streamlines Aesthetics and Feel</h2><p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30105308/Bikedrive-Air_system.jpg\" alt=\"bikedrive air system inside frame\" width=\"1620\" height=\"1080\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30105308/Bikedrive-Air_system.jpg 1620w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30105308/Bikedrive-Air_system-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30105308/Bikedrive-Air_system-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30105308/Bikedrive-Air_system-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30105308/Bikedrive-Air_system-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30105308/Bikedrive-Air_system-1536x1024.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30105308/Bikedrive-Air_system-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30105308/Bikedrive-Air_system-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30105308/Bikedrive-Air_system-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1620px) 100vw, 1620px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb20 src ng ngcb20 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30105308/Bikedrive-Air_system.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30105308/Bikedrive-Air_system.jpg 1620w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30105308/Bikedrive-Air_system-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30105308/Bikedrive-Air_system-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30105308/Bikedrive-Air_system-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30105308/Bikedrive-Air_system-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30105308/Bikedrive-Air_system-1536x1024.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30105308/Bikedrive-Air_system-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30105308/Bikedrive-Air_system-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30105308/Bikedrive-Air_system-630x420.jpg 630w\"></p><p><span>The Bikedrive Air’s calling card is its “invisibility.” It’s not only an aesthetic touch but an engineering advantage.</span></p><p><span>Integrating the motor out of sight and out of mind eliminates the clunky appearance of many e-bike motors, leaving the bike with a streamlined look. The only thing that suggests the motor inside is a control element on the top tube.</span></p><p><span>The motor should also make riders feel more balanced on the bike. Unlike some e-bike motors, which place more weight on one side of the frame or the other, the integrated mounting puts all the weight near the bike’s centerline. The innovation allows <a href=\"https://www.maxonbikedrive.com/en/home\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">maxon</a> to promise agile handling, which adds to the bike’s natural feel.</span></p><h2>maxon Bikedrive Air Performance and Rider Experience</h2><p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30105148/maxon_bikedrive_air_road_curve_LI.jpg\" alt=\"cyclist riding with maxon bikedrive air\" width=\"1200\" height=\"627\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30105148/maxon_bikedrive_air_road_curve_LI.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30105148/maxon_bikedrive_air_road_curve_LI-297x155.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30105148/maxon_bikedrive_air_road_curve_LI-800x418.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30105148/maxon_bikedrive_air_road_curve_LI-120x63.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30105148/maxon_bikedrive_air_road_curve_LI-768x401.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30105148/maxon_bikedrive_air_road_curve_LI-696x364.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30105148/maxon_bikedrive_air_road_curve_LI-1068x558.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30105148/maxon_bikedrive_air_road_curve_LI-804x420.jpg 804w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb20 src ng ngcb20 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30105148/maxon_bikedrive_air_road_curve_LI.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30105148/maxon_bikedrive_air_road_curve_LI.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30105148/maxon_bikedrive_air_road_curve_LI-297x155.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30105148/maxon_bikedrive_air_road_curve_LI-800x418.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30105148/maxon_bikedrive_air_road_curve_LI-120x63.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30105148/maxon_bikedrive_air_road_curve_LI-768x401.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30105148/maxon_bikedrive_air_road_curve_LI-696x364.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30105148/maxon_bikedrive_air_road_curve_LI-1068x558.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30105148/maxon_bikedrive_air_road_curve_LI-804x420.jpg 804w\"></p><p><span>For the Bikedrive Air, maxon focuses on rider experience rather than quantitative performance. Weight, wattage, and range are all relatively average in the category (see specs below). Then again, it’s not necessarily fair to categorize the Bikedrive Air with exterior-mounted motors.&nbsp;</span></p><p><span>That’s because the motor is designed to augment the natural cycling experience rather than alter it. In addition to optimized balance, the invisible construction delivers a Q factor of just 152-160 mm. Compare that to the typical e-bike Q factor of around 175 mm — a narrower stance will definitely help maxon-equipped machines to ride more like bicycles. </span><span>maxon also adds freewheel capability to deliver a “seamless” transition between powered and non-powered riding.&nbsp;</span></p><p><span>Finally, users can add the optional Range Extender to double the bike’s 250 Wh range. The motor uses the maxon Connect app to enable adaptable support levels, and lets users view critical data.&nbsp;</span></p><h2>The upshot: Final Thoughts on the maxon Bikedrive Air</h2><p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/30105349/maxon_bikedrive_air_road_hmi_LI.jpg\" alt=\"bikedrive air visible control element\" width=\"1200\" height=\"627\" data-ezsrcs